{"title":"Simple Solution for Vue3 meta","slug":"vue3-meta-simple-solution","tags":["vue"],"created_at":"2021-06-20T15:38:38.902Z","content":"<p>With it, you can set meta title, description, keywords, and author. Same life cycle as the component which it used in. Reset when the component <code>onUnmounted</code>. It can be used in the <code>setup</code> of the composition api, or in <code>created, mounted, and methods</code> in the traditional Vue component style.</p>\n<h2 id=\"installation\">Installation</h2>\n<p>create <code>HTMLHead.tsx</code></p>\n<pre><code class=\"language-tsx\">import {\n  reactive,\n  onBeforeUnmount,\n  Teleport,\n  getCurrentInstance,\n  ComponentInternalInstance,\n} from &#39;vue&#39;\n\nconst store = reactive({\n  title: &#39;&#39;,\n  description: &#39;&#39;,\n  keywords: &#39;&#39;,\n  author: &#39;&#39;,\n})\n\n// try to remove existing elements\ntry {\n  for (const sel of [\n    &#39;title&#39;,\n    &#39;meta[name=&quot;description&quot;]&#39;,\n    &#39;meta[name=&quot;keywords&quot;]&#39;,\n    &#39;meta[name=&quot;author&quot;]&#39;,\n  ]) {\n    const el = document.head.querySelector(sel)\n    if (el) {\n      el.remove()\n    }\n  }\n} catch (error) {}\n\nexport function HTMLHead() {\n  return (\n    &lt;Teleport to=&quot;head&quot;&gt;\n      {store.title &amp;&amp; &lt;title&gt;{store.title}&lt;/title&gt;}\n      {store.description &amp;&amp; (\n        &lt;meta name=&quot;description&quot; content={store.description} /&gt;\n      )}\n      {store.keywords &amp;&amp; &lt;meta name=&quot;keywords&quot; content={store.keywords} /&gt;}\n      {store.author &amp;&amp; &lt;meta name=&quot;author&quot; content={store.author} /&gt;}\n    &lt;/Teleport&gt;\n  )\n}\n\nexport const useTitle = generateUseFunction(&#39;title&#39;)\nexport const useDescription = generateUseFunction(&#39;description&#39;)\nexport const useKeywords = generateUseFunction(&#39;keywords&#39;)\nexport const useAuthor = generateUseFunction(&#39;author&#39;)\n\nfunction generateUseFunction(name: string) {\n  return (value: string, vm?: ComponentInternalInstance) =&gt; {\n    // @ts-ignore\n    store[name] = value\n    const thevm = vm || getCurrentInstance()\n    if (!thevm) {\n      throw new Error(\n        `HTMLHead use ${name}: the second argument is required when called outside of setup`\n      )\n    }\n    onBeforeUnmount(() =&gt; {\n      // @ts-ignore\n      if (store[name] === value) {\n        // @ts-ignore\n        store[name] = &#39;&#39;\n      }\n    }, thevm)\n  }\n}\n</code></pre>\n<p>import <code>HTMLHead</code> component and append to your root component, such as <code>App.vue</code></p>\n<pre><code class=\"language-vue\">&lt;template&gt;\n  &lt;div id=&quot;app&quot;&gt;\n    &lt;HTMLHead /&gt;\n  &lt;/div&gt;\n&lt;/template&gt;\n\n&lt;script&gt;\n  import { HTMLHead } from &#39;./HTMLHead.tsx&#39;\n  export default {\n    components: { HTMLHead },\n  }\n&lt;/script&gt;\n</code></pre>\n<h2 id=\"usage\">Usage</h2>\n<pre><code class=\"language-ts\">import {\n  useTitle,\n  useDescription,\n  useKeywords,\n  useAuthor,\n} from &#39;./HTMLHead.tsx&#39;\n</code></pre>\n<p>In <code>setup</code></p>\n<pre><code class=\"language-ts\">setup() {\n  useTitle(&#39;title text&#39;)\n}\n</code></pre>\n<blockquote>\n<p>:warning: The second argument is required if used in asynchronous setup or outside of setup.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>In <code>created</code>, <code>mounted</code>, <code>methods</code></p>\n<pre><code class=\"language-ts\">created() {\n  useTitle(&#39;title text&#39;, this)\n}\n</code></pre>\n<p>After await in asynchronous setup</p>\n<pre><code class=\"language-ts\">async setup() {\n  const vm = getCurrentInstance()\n  await something\n  useTitle(&#39;title text&#39;, vm)\n}\n</code></pre>\n<p>Please tell me if you have more elegant code.</p>\n","category_id":"1","category":{"name":"Front-end","id":"1","slug":"frontend","alternate":{"en":"frontend","zh":"frontend"}},"alternate":{"en":"vue3-meta-simple-solution","zh":"vue3-meta-simple-solution"}}